- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes a large longitudinal Twitter dataset to study political polarization on social media. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper may involve software tools and techniques for data collection, processing, and analysis. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper deals with the social and political implications of social media use. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a less likely category but still relevant as the paper may involve computational methods and models for analyzing social media data. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a less likely category as the paper may involve natural language processing techniques for analyzing political discourse on Twitter.
